The model uses **{{ n_features|int }} socio-economic features**. The unexplained variance — **{{ ((1 - r2) * 100)|round(0)|int }}%** — represents service variation that cannot be predicted from demographics. This "residual" variance is policy-driven: it reflects the accumulated effect of historical investment decisions, operator commercial strategies, planning permissions, and subsidy choices that do not follow demographic logic. This is a critical finding: **53–72% of the bus coverage pattern across England is not demographically determined — it is the result of policy choices that could, in principle, be changed.**
